Q¿A BPOL ist eine Lern-App für Smartphones, die ausgewählten Nutzern der Bundespolizeidirektion Flughafen Frankfurt/Main zur Verfügung gestellt wird.

Das Lernspiel beruht auf dem gängigen Quiz-Prinzip wie bei „Wer wird Millionär“ und „Quizduell“. Die Lernenden beantworten Fragen aus unterschiedlichen Themen - von Luftsicherheit über Grenzpolizei bis hin zu Verwaltungs-,Organisations- und Fun-Fragen. Mit der App können Lernende ihr Wissen allein oder im Duell testen.

Ziel ist es mit der App selbstgesteuertes Lernen, an jedem Ort, zu jeder Zeit sowie eine Steigerung des Wissens in spielerischer Form zu fördern. Für die Lernenden gilt es im Wettbewerb mit Anderen ein möglichst hohes Ranking zu erreichen; so simpel wie fesselnd.

放送時間になったらアプリを立ち上げるだけ！

QT-5 Rush is an action game about robots.

The game gives you vast possibilities to customize your own robot using 6 properties.

You can get almost 50 different pieces of equipment, which can be mixed into a thousand combinations.

In the game, you will find abundant robotic hardware and unique skills, 4 planet scenes, each with their particular boss.

Story:On an abandoned planet, there are still a small amount of resources.

Some robots were left to finish the collection.

A revolution against human’s domination was broken out since some robots suddenly gained the ability of logic.

Except for you—loyal Alex—a robot with high study ability. So you became the enemy of those ambitious robots.

Can you rescue Dr. S and  revenge your good friend, Halley?

Who gave those robots the logic ability?

These mysteries are expecting for you to unravel…

QTS Wizard - Mental Arithmetic is a multiple-choice based Maths Quiz program designed for an audience who are interested in additional training resources for preparing the Professional Skills Test in the UK with an aim of achieving the Qualified Teaching Status (QTS).  Specifically, this program provides a set of mental arithmetic questions typical in the QTS Numeracy test for the users to practise and improve their skills and techniques.
 
App Features:
 
*  Over 50 types of mental arithmetic multiple-choice questions, organised in 3 categories:
   -- Arithmetic
   -- Fractions, Decimals and Percentages
   -- Time, Money and Conversion
*  Powerful question generation engine: all questions are parameterised and auto-generated, providing virtually unlimited possibilities.
*  3 modes: Free Play, Time Trial, and Quiz Play.
*  Save user reports in pdf for Time Trial and Quiz Play.
*  Create worksheets in printable pdf for offline usage.
*  Share reports and worksheets by Email and Air Print.
*  Highly Customisable.  For example, option to select a specific maths category, or all 3 categories, for the generated questions.
*  Option to restrict access (by hiding) to the Reports and Worksheets functions.
*  Performance monitoring for each maths categories.
*  Universal App - works on iPhone and iPad devices.

Customers, thank you for your support. If you find this app useful, please rate and give us a review!

Disclaimers:
*  This program is not affiliated with the official QTS exam board or the UK Department of Education. 
*  This program does not mimic the exact format of the QTS Mental Arithmetic test; i.e. the questions are presented in a multiple choice format instead of a verbal format.
*  This program does not cater for the Literacy section of the QTS test.


      more

QTS Wizard - Written Data and Arithmetic is a multiple-choice based Maths Quiz program designed for an audience who are interested in achieving the Qualified Teaching Status (QTS) by sitting the Professional Skills Test in the UK.  Specifically, this program provides a set of typical written data and arithmetic questions for the users to practise and improve the skills and techniques required in the QTS Numeracy written test.
 
App Features:
 
- Over 50 types of multiple-choice based written data and arithmetic questions, organised in 3 categories:
   -- Table and Data 
   -- Graphs and Charts (bar charts, box-and-whisker diagrams, cumulative frequency graphs, line graphs, pie charts and scatter graphs)
   -- Arithmetic 
-  Powerful question generation engine: all questions are parameterised and auto-generated, providing virtually unlimited possibilities.
- 3 modes: Free Play, Time Trial, and Quiz Play.
- Save user reports in pdf for Time Trial and Quiz Play.
- Create worksheets in printable pdf for offline usage.
- Share reports and worksheets by Email and Air Print.
- Highly Customisable.  For example, option to select a specific maths category, or all 3 categories, for the generated questions.
- Option to restrict access (by hiding) to the Reports and Worksheets functions.
- Performance monitoring for each maths categories.
- Universal App - works on iPhone and iPad devices.

Customers, thank you for your support. If you find this app useful, please rate and give us a review!

Disclaimers:
*  This program is not affiliated with the official QTS exam board or the UK Department of Education. 
*  This program provides multiple choice as an answering format and does not provide other formats such as "fill in the bank", "drag and drop" or "hot spot".
*  This program does not cater for the Literacy section of the QTS test.

Mô tả
Qua sông IQ 2 là phiên bản tiếp theo của tựa game IQ nổi tiếng Qua sông IQ. 
Game gồm tập hợp rất nhiều câu đố trí tuệ siêu khó. 
Thu thập những ngôi sao trong từng màn chơi để mở khóa những Block tiếp theo. 
Chinh phục tất cả các màn chơi trong thời gian ngắn nhất để trở thành người đứng đầu “Bảng xếp hạng” IQ.
Dữ liệu phong phú.
Update thường xuyên.
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/quasongiq
Website: http://gamemost.vn/
********* Kiến Trúc Game *********
Hiện tại game có 10 Block với 32 Logic khác nhau.
Hệ thống thành tựu phong phú độc đáo.
Bảng xếp hạng chỉ số IQ của từng người chơi.
Người chơi tích lũy càng nhiều "sao" và tổng thời gian chơi của các bàn càng ngắn thì xếp hạng càng cao.

Nhấn vào Biểu tượng của từng Logic để chọn màn chơi tương ứng

Nhấn vào nút “Help” để biết luật chơi cho từng màn chơi.

Nhấn vào nút “Share” để chụp ảnh màn hình, chia sẻ với bạn bè trên facebook.

Qua Sông Phá Án - Giải Đố Logic - Thử thách IQ
-----------------------------------------------

Giải mã những câu đố logic, tập làm thám tử điều tra phá án!

Game mở ra những câu đố hay ho hóm hỉnh hiểm hóc hãi hùng!

Bạn phải suy luận đau đầu hại não nhằm tìm ra cách qua sông, đưa người đưa vật qua sông.

Những vụ án ly kỳ bí ẩn đang chờ được điều tra phá án truy lùng thủ phạm.

Những mật mã hóc búa rắc rối cần được mở khóa.

Câu chuyện về các vụ án truy bắt tội phạm hay câu đố trinh thám luôn có sức hút mê hoặc đối với nhiều người. Chắc hẳn thời thơ ấu, bạn đã từng mơ ước trở thành một thám tử lừng danh với biệt tài phá án siêu khủng?

Hãy thử tài phán đoán của mình qua các nhiệm vụ trong game, chúng sẽ giúp bạn gia tăng và cải thiện được khả năng tư duy logic, phán đoán và kích thích phát triển não bộ.

Thường xuyên giải đáp và luyện tập những câu đố logic sẽ giúp bạn phản ứng nhanh hơn trước các thử thách của cuộc sống.
Nhiều câu đố cấp tiểu học dường như rất đơn giản nhưng đôi khi người lớn hay thậm chí cả thiên tài cũng chưa chắc giải đáp nhanh được.

Có những câu hỏi cực kỳ hóc búa khiến bạn phải nghi ngờ chính IQ của mình.

Thử tài thám tử với những vụ án có hiện trường dàn dựng tinh vi, liệu bạn có giải được?

Những câu đố tưởng không khó mà khó không tưởng.
Những câu đố tưởng không dễ mà dễ không tưởng.

Mời các bạn cùng tham gia!

Quad is an entertaining and addicting number based game. The objective is simple, just add numbers of the same kind together. By doing this, you eliminate rows above you which fulfills the overall goal. 

Quad attempts to amalgamate math and enjoyment. You will want to keep adding numbers together, again and again. In addition to being addicting, Quad doesn’t require coordination, so anyone can play it without getting frustrated. However, if your addition skills are a bit rusty, you can use the colors instead.

Everything from the color scheme to the title bar was meticulously crafted. The title actually changes based on what information you need the most. And the colors were specifically chosen to provide visual cues that allow more user friendly gameplay.

We have specifically directed certain types of gameplay to different types of players. Original mode was the first type, and it gets intensely fast paced. However, after experiencing this pace we determined that an easier game mode would be beneficial for non-gamers, that's what Leisure mode is. The result is highly favorable.

Introducing, brand new Puzzle Game - QUAD 36.

HOW TO PLAY:
---------------
A random of 1 to 9 numbers need to arrange in each QUAD. 
A QUAD is a collection of 4 cells. There are 5 BLUE QUADS and 4 YELLOW QUADS.  
BLUE QUADS bubble-up when all MATCHING Numbers are arranged and YELLOW QUADS bubble-up when a SEQUENCE of Numbers gets arranged. 

SCORING:
----------
For each new number added to the board, score INCREASES by the value of itself.
For each existing number that re-arranged on the board, score DECREASES by itself if the score is greater than 100 Points.
For each Bubble-Up, score raises up by 50 Points.

A Quadcopter / Multirotor RC Drone simulator with First Person View (FPV), HUD, Return Home, Course Lock, Home Lock, Camera Gimbal, Acro mode, Acro 3D mode  and more..Now Google Cardboard VR is also supported for immersive flying and FPV experience.Support for ControllersPlease note that this a simulator and Not a game. It is designed for RC enthusiasts to practice Flying skills. Basic Tutorial for beginner is in the above description video.Features:1) Based on real physics Model of Quadcopter2) Interactive selection of different cameras modes:    * Eye level Camera   * First Person View Camera   * Stabilized Gimbal Camera   * Follow Camera      You can walk around while flying, looking at the quad either by dragging the middle of screen or by enabling accelerometer button on the left side in the Eye level Camera Mode..3) Return to Location (RTL) When on the Quad will automatically Return and Land back in its Landing Position. It will Automatically switch on when the Quad goes out of range.4) Position HoldWhen ON the Quad will try to Hold its position when both control sticks are released.5) Course Lock When ON the Forward, Backward, Left and Right  will remain same regardless of orientation of Quad. e.g. Moving Right stick Forward will always make the Quad go forward in East Direction even if its pointing towards north.6) Home Lock When ON the Forward will always be Away from you and Backwards will always be towards you regardless of Quads Orientation.7) Heads up Display(HUD)    Displaying real-time Pitch, Roll, Heading, Altitude and Speed.8) Adjustable Control sensitivity Settings9) Auto Stabilizing adjustable10) Altitude Hold Switch   If ON the quad will try to maintain the altitude when it was switched on. 11) Advanced Settings   If enabled users can change the Total Weight, Static / Dynamic thrust, PID setting and Aerodynamic Drag values.12) Multiple Quad / Scene Selection / Some basic Challenges for Time Pass..13) Multiple mode Input Support.Now it supports mode1, mode2. mode3, mode4 and accelerometers. You can change via settings page14) Camera rotation in FPV and Gimbal camera.Click and Drag from center of screen on FPV or Gimbal camera. Double click in center to reset. 15) Dynamic WindWind effect will reduce when behind the building.16) Google cardboard Support for immersive virtual reality and FPV experience.Make sure that you have a controller attached to the device because the only way you can control the quadcopter is by controller once the Cardboard VR is enabled.  After enabling you have to gaze at the buttons on the UI and press the trigger button on the cardboard to click it. Once you are flying then pressing the trigger anywhere will open the settings page. You can also touch on screen anywhere to execute trigger event instead of pressing the trigger button.17) Max Tilt Angle  / Auto Stabilize Sensitivity SliderIn Normal Mode the slider changes the Maximum Tilt angle setting. This settings determines the maximum roll / pitch angle the quadcopter will tilt. In Sports Mode it changes the Auto Stabilize sensitivity. The higher the settings the more force is applied to stabilize the quadcopter.18) Acro / Acro 3d mode for expert flyingAuto stabilize will not be applied in these modes. You need to be expert to fly in this mode.In 3D Mode is mode in which the Quadcopter can fly upside down also. The throttle sticks will produce reverse thrust when moved down from the center position. Enjoy Flying..Credits: Some Arteria content is in use.

column6:
Please welcome another great time-killer game!!!

At each level of the game you will be presented a pattern that must be solved to its initial state. At the beginning of the game the pattern is mixed.

Each level in the game is presented in the form of a square field with tiles, which form a pattern. The game has a set of levels with tiles of the same color, as well as multi-color sets.

The controls are quite simple: tap your finger onto the row or column and slide the row / column towards the necessary number of cells. Cyclic shift, i.e. when the tile disappears on one side of the field, it appears on the other side.

You can log in to Facebook, to see your friend's ratings, and the world rankings. The more levels you open, the higher your rating is.

Can you reach the three pyramids? 

If you like rhythm-based platformer games, this one will rock your world, not because it's in 3D, but because it's insanely addictive! This game provides fast-paced 3D platformer experience along with "impossible" game challenges that's more accessible to newcomers. 

With simple "touch to play" experience, it will keep you entertained if you are on the train, on a bus, or simply when taking breaks. This is more of a casual style, fast-paced, adventurous, action platformer game. Each level has a progress bar to help you track your progress. 

Your jumping cube flips through obstacles to reach its final destination: the ol' mighty pyramids! Do your best to avoid spikes, moving objects, 3D enemies, moving platforms, ramps and much more. The main objective is to stay alive and flip your way through obstacles to reach your final destination. 

You can play with 3 different cube types: 
- double jump cube (red cube)
- triple jump cube (dark red cube)
- quadruple jump cube (very dark, cherry color cube)

Each jumping cube has its jumping limits while in the air. Once it reaches the ground, the jump limit resets itself and you can jump again. This is what makes this gameplay unique and entertaining. For each cube type, there are special levels to play with. Quadruple jump cube has levels that can be complete only if the cube can quadruple jump. Triple jump cube levels are suitable for triple and quadruple jump cubes, and so on.. There are many level variations for each cube abilities. 

There are also PRACTICE levels to sharpen your skills. Those practice levels are shorter version of the longer levels. They are more "snackable" and easier to complete, but once you go to the longer levels to reach the ol' might pyramids is not easy. 

Insanely addictive and FREE TO PLAY!

The 9-hole golf course at Quail Ridge uses a traditional, classic design approach that leverages the natural beauty of its secluded New England surroundings.Quail Ridge was nominated for the 2006 Golf Digest “Best new private golf courses in America” contest. The course was also the site for the Massachusetts Golf Association Mid-Amateur qualifying event in August 2006. Quail Ridge is receiving many accolades for the beauty and challenge of the course layout.

Cut into 94 acres of mature pine trees and hardwood forest, the course is bounded by conservation land and water. Quail Ridge is secluded and serene. It appeals to golfers of any age and ability.

The course was architected by Mr. Mark Mungeam, a principal in the nationally-acclaimed golf course architect firm of Cornish, Silva, and Mungeam, Inc. Mr. Mungeam is nationally-known for his course renovation work at Olympia Fields Country Club for the 1997 Senior Open and the 2003 US Open, and his course renovation work at The Broadmoor for the 1996 U.S. Women’s Open. He describes Quail Ridge as “a beautiful New England course on a wonderful piece of property. The design fits the course naturally into the surrounding land. It is serene and challenging for any level of player.”

A CLASSIC GOLF EXPERIENCE
There are many aspects to the Quail Ridge golfing experience that you’ll find unique and attractive. Quail Ridge has a chipping area and putting green. Quail Ridge also offers a full array of childrens’ programs.

A REWARDING, BALANCED DESIGN
The golf course at Quail Ridge encourages you to think about every shot, balancing risk and reward. Holes vary in distance and angle, making it attractive to both long hitters and shot-makers; some holes favor a fade, while others reward a draw. Sweeping elevation changes and rock formations add to the experience. Quail Ridge has a balanced blend of hazards, including water, bunkers, wetlands, and New England woods. You’ll find this course both challenging and fun.

Quan Game is a game inspired by the traditional and folkloric game from Vietnam Ô ăn quan (also called O an quan or Mandarin Capturing Game).

The game was mainly played by children because it can be played anywhere with just some pebbles, chips or seeds, a tray of at least 12 boxes or by drawing a tray on the ground.

The game has crossed the Asian borders and is increasingly played, especially since its adaptation as a smartphone app, in the same way as the democratization of Sudoku and Sokoban japanese games.

Quan Game is playable by all ages, is fun, casual, strategic and educational. Several tactics are possible, calculate the best possible move to win the most points, to ensure that the opponent can not empty the Mandarin boxes...


The historical origin of the game is not clearly defined, but has been played for a very long time by Vietnamese children and is similar to the African game Mancala.


Game Features:
► Simplified interface
► Easy to play
► Player against Player
► Player vs. Computer


Rules of the game:
► The player who have the most points wins the game
► The game board consists of two large Mandarin boxes (neutral) and five boxes for each player
► The game ends when both Mandarin boxes are empty, each player gets the remaining pieces from the boxes they own before determining the winner
► At each turn, each player must move one of their five non-empty squares to an adjacent square
 - The player takes all the pieces in the box, then adds one piece in each adjacent box, continuing in the same direction
 - If the last box is followed by two empty boxes, the round ends
 - If the next box is empty, the player takes ("eat") the points of the box after, and continues to eat as much as possible (empty box then full box)
 - If the following box is not empty, the player remakes the same thing that at the beginning of the turn
► If at the beginning of a round, a player has no coin, he takes 5 points from his score and puts a coin in each of his boxes

Quantum 3 is an educational match-3 game for all ages where fun meets quantum physics! Build subatomic particles, learn about the mysteries of fundamental physics and deploy antimatter to clear the way! You'll match and swap quarks to make (and learn about) the baryons you need for each objective. Puzzle out the quantum properties of color, flavor and spin. So get in there and start your quantum-venture! Quantum 3 is puzzle-matching at its finest and a great intro to the world of particle physics! The game is free-to-play with no in-app purchases. The game is developed at Michigan State University by the Games for Entertainment and Learning Lab and is funded under grant PHY 1653405 by the National Science Foundation.

Drag different sliders to determine the probability of a drum sound occurrence. Experiment with a range of unusual and quirky sounds.  Set the maximum and minimum of each parameter to create sounds that vary with each hit. Add sloppiness and randomized accent for a more human feel. Deep exploration of this drum machine's features reveals lots of surprises.

Created by Graham Franz.

Quantum Lake is a mesmerizing voyage into the depths of a mysterious labyrinth set somewhere in outer space. 

Drive your cosmic fish shoals across 25 different scenarios of growing complexity, avoiding your enemies and reaching for the energy crystals. 

Collect as many coins as possible and choose between 5 different cosmic fish species: Quantum, Gamma Ray, Proton, Electron and Plutonium, each with different abilities.

Avoid electric fields and take advantage of the wormholes to teleport into different areas of the labyrinth, but mind your many enemies: like matter and anti-matter, bright and dark fishes will annihilate themselves upon contact. 

Quantum Lake is a game designed and developed by Damiano Gui. Music and sound effects by Eric Matyas.

In the depths of space, containment fields are degrading and spectres are threatening to break free. To re-establish containment, you must solve laser puzzles. Use mirrors, lenses, and more to guide laser beams to colored targets in this scientifically accurate and wildly cool laser game. Watch out for the spectres... they will haunt you.

Quantum Spectre challenges players to solve increasingly tricky puzzles. Each new puzzle requires players to demonstrate a deeper intuition about the behavior of light and an understanding of the optics tools. Quantum Spectre is part of the Leveling Up collection, developed by EdGE and to support and measure science learning in games people choose to play in their free time.

EdGE — On the edge of science and play! The Educational Gaming Environments group (EdGE) at TERC hopes to show that learning happens in all kinds of places by investigating the possibilities—and challenging the assumptions—of game-based learning environments. EdGE is designing and studying games whose mechanics mirror real scientific phenomena, but more importantly, are fun to play. 

EdGE at TERC Copyright 2013. 
Work made possible by funding from the National Science Foundation (DRK12 grant #1119144). Any opinions, findings, and conclusions or recommendations expressed in this material are those of the authors and do not necessarily reflect views of the National Science Foundation.

Quantum TiqTaqToe is what you get when you combine TicTacToe with quantum effects. The result is a fun game that makes you wonder how you could ever go back to just classical TicTacToe. You'll build an intuition for the strangeness of the quantum realm, without ever needing to learn quantum physics, by using superpositions and entanglement. Can you use quantum to turn a losing game into a winning one?Unlock the full version to enable a stronger quantum AI, remove ads, and... get access to the online mode so you can test your quantum skills remotely with your friends!If you're interested in using TiqTaqToe for educational purposes, please reach out.

TicTacToe in TicTacToe!  In order to secure a move on the main board, you have to win the inner game inside that spot.  AND you can jump around as you want to play in the all the different zones whenever you want!  Fun!  That adds a whole new level to the game!  You have to decide if you want to let each cell tie up or if you want to go off and give up that cell, for the opportunity to win another one.

You think you know everyting there is to know about driving? Quarry Driver 3 will make you think again! This third installment in the unique parking simulator series puts you into shoes of a mine worker. You will drive the biggest, most demanding vehicles known to men. They're heavy, they're powerful, they can hold their own in the most uninviting terrain!

With 50 different mission, the game will let you explore an environment unlike anything you're used to. Steep slopes, sharp turns and unpredictable terrain will demand your full attention, all the time. Give it your best and prove yourself as a driver capable of anything!

10 POWERFUL TRUCKS
Quarry Driver 3 is no place for meager cars. Each and every one of the available vehicles is an unstoppable force that you will get to control. Wheel loaders, excavators, crushers, offroad trucks - you name it, we have it!

DEMANDING COURSES
All of the missions take place in a quarry mine. This means there are no easy to drive roads with wide lanes. You will have to watch carefully and adapt to the situation.

REALISTIC GRAPHICS
The whole environment comes to life thanks to beautifully rendered environment. The quarry you'll be exploring looks busy and worked in.

FREE TO PLAY
The Main Game Mode is 100% FREE to play, all the way through, no strings attached! Extra Game Modes which alter the rules slightly to make the game easier are available through optional In-App Purchases. Each mode has separate leaderboards to make for totally fair competition!

GAME FEATURES
▶ IMPRESSIVE CAR COLLECTION : Drive 10 Awesome Cars
▶ PRO PARKING MISSIONS: Huge campaign to beat, earn in-game money for your progres
▶ 100% Free to Play Missions
▶ CONTROLS: Buttons, Wheel, Tilt & MFi Game Controller Support
▶ CAMERAS: Multiple cameras including First Person view for full immersion
▶ iCLOUD: Supports play between your devices & automatic progress backup with iCloud

Quarto is a simple board game, but can be very hard to master.This version has advanced AI opponents.

Quarta is an original digital board game with a unique generative soundtrack, designed and created by Kennerspiel des Jahres nominated game designer Brett J. Gilbert and musician, software designer and Bloom co-creator Peter Chilvers.

Two players take turns to place tiles, build areas of coloured ‘quarta’s, and claim those areas to control the three colours. Each game lasts only a few minutes, and is played until the tiles fill a 5×5 square. The winner is the player who controls the most colours at the end of the game.

But Quarta is also something more. As you play, Quarta creates a totally unique piece of music – an individual soundtrack for every game – driven by the arrangement of areas built by the players.


"Both challenging to the mind and relaxing at the same time, the perfect form of gaming." AppAdvice


KEY FEATURES

• Designed for digital: A brand new two-player tile game created especially for iOS.

• Simple, engaging gameplay: Tutorial gets you playing in 60 seconds. A game takes a few minutes.

• Unique generative soundtrack: A new piece of music created every time you play.

• Sophisticated, dynamic AI: In ‘Solo’ mode, players will discover a strong, adaptive AI opponent, which refines its play as they improve and provides a satisfying opponent for even the most experienced players.

• Listen mode: In ‘Listen’ mode players can simply watch and enjoy a unique piece of generative music.


ABOUT THE CREATORS

Brett J. Gilbert (game design & visual design) is a professional game designer. His first board game, Divinare, published by Asmodee in 2012, was recommended by the Spiel des Jahres 2013 jury. Elysium, published in 2015 by Space Cowboys, has been nominated for the Kennerspiel des Jahres award. Quarta is his first digital game.

Peter Chilvers (iOS development & soundtrack design) is a musician and software designer. Best known for creating the iOS apps Bloom, Trope and Scape with Brian Eno, he has also toured with Karl Hyde (Underworld) and recorded a number of albums with vocalist Tim Bowness.

column1: Quation: The fun game of equations!
column6: Who knew math equations were fun?  The object is to place all the tiles in their correct place to make all the equations true.  Simple, right?  Maybe not as simple as you think!  Try it, you'll be addicted to trying to get all the equations correct within the allowed number of moves.  Earning Game Dots will get you through 10 levels to be a Quation master!Object of Game                     Complete all 10 Levels (50 Game Dots) in the fewest number of moves.  You play by moving the purple tiles to the correct place on the board.  But be careful, there may be more than one way to make an equation correct.  You have to be able get all the tiles to the board and have 5 correct equations!How to Earn Game DotsA Game Dot is earned when you complete a board within the number of moves allowed for that board.  You can see how many moves are allowed at the bottom of the board along with the number of moves you have already taken.  Once the number of moves taken turns red, you have gone over the allowed moves for that board.  You will still need to finish the board to continue on to a new board and try again.

Quatrix is a fusion of backgammon and checkers with a hint of chess and offers hours of challenge, fun, and strategic learning to gamers -- young developing minds and discriminating adults. Different from many new games today, Quatrix respects your intelligence, judgement and skill level, encouraging different avenues of engagement with every outing. Purity of mechanics, multiplicity of maneuvers, and random dice rolls ensure that no two games are ever alike!

Quatrix is a two player board game which you can play on your device with a friend ("Pass and Play") or with a computer opponent.

The object of the game is to be the first to get your pieces to the other side of the board. There are two types of pieces in the game of Quatrix: rings and discs. When combined they form a 'Pip' (Piece in Piece). All pieces can move forward, backward, or sideways. See the tutorial in the app for more details. The full rules can also be found on our website at www.playquatrix.com.

A new puzzle revolution for iPod touch, iPhone and iPad. Quatro! is a more modern adaptation of the wildly popular board game Quarto, invented by Swiss mathematician Blaise Müller. 

The aim of the game is to get four pieces in a row that all have at least one property in common. In this case, one reaches a Quatro. And of course, you should get a Quatro on that board before your opponent does. This may seem simple, but once you dive into the wonderful world of Quatro, you will find that timing is crucial, attention is critical and strategy is key. 

Play against an immensely smart computer (that is also adjustable to dummy-level,) against a friend on the same device or against your friends elsewhere via Game Center, and become a Quatro-master. 

Awesome math facts about the game:
- For the first move (i.e. picking the initial piece) there are 16 possibilities. In the next move this piece can be put on 16 places and one of the remaining 15 pieces can be chosen. An upper limit for the total search space is thus
16. (16.15).(15.14). … . (2.1).1 = (16!)2 = 4.4e26 (this number has a lot of zeros!). A complete check of the board would take a 500 MHz computer 280 billion years.
- The number of distinct Quatro’s in classic mode (only in rows and columns and the main diagonals) is 414298141056 winning Quatro’s, whereas the extreme mode (classic mode + winning positions in squares) holds approximately 18596841216 winning board configurations.
- If both players play optimally, the game will eventually end up in a draw, but I dare say that such a optimal state will never be reached. Just because of the mathematics.

PS: These calculations probably need some sort of check, please contact me if you should find different outcomes!

What I am currently doing to improve gameplay in future versions:
- Multiple themes (Space theme, Sushi theme and more)
- A play-reward system.
- Crazy game variations such as 5x5 boards!

I would love to hear from you, users, what might be improved or what suggestions you might have to increase the Quatro-experience!

Design by SOS Design Studio Hilversum.
Developed by Vincent Roest.

Quatros Origins is a block puzzle game that tries to reconnect with the good old days where classic arcade games were easy to play, but hard to master!The objective of the game, is to manipulate tetromino- and pentomino blocks, and placing them strategically to make at least one full horizontal line. At first sight it looks like a 2D game, but with each block you place, the platform will turn ninety degrees, giving you four playing fields. But every piece will affect every side!

Quatt is a two player board game.

It is played on a 4×4 board. There are 16 unique pieces, each of which is either:

- tall or short
- red or blue
- square or circular
- hollow or solid.

Players take turns choosing a piece which the other player must then place on the board. A player wins by placing a piece on the board which forms a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal row of four pieces, all of which have a common attribute (all short, all circular, etc.)

How well do you know the Barcelona Subway?
Can you identify the station from the photo?
All stations of the Barcelona Metro in a fascinating photo quiz.
Guess all stations of the Barcelona Metro and make no mistake!

The Barcelona Metro (Catalan and Spanish: Metro de Barcelona) is an unofficial brand name for an extensive network of rapid transit electrified railway lines that run mostly underground in central Barcelona and into the city's suburbs. It is part of the larger public transport system of Barcelona, the capital of Catalonia (Spain), with unified fares under the Autoritat del Transport Metropolità (ATM) scheme. As of 2014, the network is operated by two separate companies: Transports Metropolitans de Barcelona (TMB) and Ferrocarrils de la Generalitat de Catalunya (FGC). It is made up of 12 lines, combining the lines owned by the two companies. Two lines, L9 and L10 are being built at present, with both lines having different sections of each opened between 2009 and 2016. They are due to be completed in the near future. Three lines on the network have opened as automatic train operation/driverless vehicle systems since 2009: Line 11, Line 9 and Line 10, in chronological order.

Ein Frage-Antwort-Quiz, in dem pro Runde mit zehn Fragen dein Wissen getestet wird. Von den vier Antworten ist nur eine richtig, wobei dir ein 50/50- und Statistik-Joker helfen. Zwei Bonusfragen pro Runde geben dir eventuelle Extrapunkte.

Zu Beginn sind 100 kostenlose Zufallsfragen aus allen Bereichen enthalten. Zusätzliche Fragenpakete mit je 4000 neuen, thematisch sortierten Fragen können in der QuizDeluxe-App erworben und installiert werden.

Im Duell Modus können auf dem iPad zwei Spieler direkt gegeneinander antreten, eine große Multiplayer Runde ermöglicht Spielspass mit vielen Freunden gleichzeitig.

Neben der Highscoreliste können zudem nun über 40 Erfolge im GameCenter erspielt werden.

Die universal APP läuft auf iPhone, iPad und Apple Watch und benötigt mindestens iOS V7.

The final version of the quick-press quiz is finally here!

While enjoying the quiz with friends and family,
Let's collect points and aim for higher ranking!


【function】
・You can play online against other users (1:1)
・You can also play AI (computer) battles
・You can answer not only by selecting characters but also by voice.
・You can also play cooperative games in collaboration mode
・You can also do a score attack where everyone competes for the score.
・You can also do a time attack where everyone competes for time.
・You can make rooms and play online with friends and family
・Points will accumulate when you compete
・You can get Ruby if you accumulate points in the match
・If you collect rubies, you can exchange them for items such as stamps and backgrounds.
・You can set the exchanged stamps on the setting screen and use them during the battle.
・New quizzes will be added daily
・You can check the transition of the number of quizzes in the graph.

・It's a chance for DL ​​because big advertisements are not displayed only for now

・You can follow your favorite users and friends
・If there is an unwanted user, you can block it.
・You can release the block from the blocked list on the setting screen.
・Others (Terms of use, inquiries, user violation report)



[Additional features]
・Player correct answer rate can be seen

・A new collaboration (cooperative play) will be possible.
・You will receive new function push notifications.
・It will be possible to take over when changing models
・The room function will be expanded so that 3 or more people can play against each other.
・You can choose the strength of the computer in AI battle

・You will get a login bonus
・Daily mission will be added

A Quiz game with a strategic twist!Use power-ups and boosts to outsmart your opponent - the key to win however is to answer correct on the questions.No registration - instant action - easy to start - hard to master.GAME DETAILS          ===========You are a farmer that plants carrots - make sure your opponent don't turn them into rabbits. Choose a field that is available.Answer the question - correct answer gives you points and the field together with a new carrot. Incorrect answer gives birth to a new rabbit.Catch the opponents rabbits by placing carrots on each side and answer correct.Bonus streaks for correct answers.Power-ups - is the question to hard? Switch it out, use 50/50 or more time so you can ask a friend.Boosts - numerous fields gives you 2x, 3x, 5x points. Use it to your advantage.Twists - You can set out solid stones, set off bombs, dig a really deep hole on and more!  But you can only use them once / game. So use them smart!Good luck - GO!

Quizen is like most other quiz apps, except that where other have thousands of questions we have millions and enable more freedom for you to search, browse, and create your own quizzes. One simple way to engage with Quizen is to start taking the Weekly Challenge, where Quizen will launch 10 questions every day each week for all to compete with each other. But Quizen enables you to take quizzes on almost anything, and you can also:•	Choose among 6 000 categories (example: American 19th century poets.)•	Create a quiz (example: Music + Pop + 1980s)•	Generate a quiz on specific topics (example: Depeche Mode, Clint Eastwood etc)When your friends connect to Quizen, you can challange them on anything. But you will also soon be able to compete against strangers, perhaps someone from the other side of the world who take the same quiz as you do but in her language.

Quizen Party is a real-time version of Quizen. Party enables you to join one quiz session with your friends and compete in real-time on topics you all have added to the quiz.Quizen enables you to compete on almost anything, and you and your friends can for instance:-         Choose among 6 000 categories (example: American 19th century poets)-         Create a quiz (example: Music + Pop + 1980s)-         Generate a quiz on specific topics (example: Depeche Mode, Clint Eastwood etc)Scenario example: You have invited some friends to dinner. After dinner you propose to have some fun and compete on quizzes. You tell your friends to download Quizen Party while you create a new session in Quizen Party. You then show your friends the QR code created for the session or read them the code you have on your mobile screen. You can see your friends on your screen as they start to enter the lobby for the session. You all take a minute to add one category or topic each. When everyone is done you start the quiz and the countdown begin. You all have your mobile phones and can see questions number 1 as it appears on each screen at the same time. When your friends have all answered the question a screen appears on each phone where you can all see who was right and wrong and the total score after the first question. You complete the quiz where the questions are a mix of all the categories/topics you have added together.! Being an early user of Party, you will have an unlimited version, meaning no limits in how many people can join the quiz, the number of questions per quiz, and the number of quizzes per day you can run.

Quiz Spiel mit verschiedenen Schwierigkeitsgraden

Zwei Spieler treten gegeneinander an. Den Kandidaten werden abwechselnd Fragen gestellt, jede Quizrunde (ein Fragenpaar) steht unter einem bestimmten Thema. Das Thema wird abwechselnd von den Spielern ausgewählt.  Es besteht die Möglichkeit zwischen vier angebotenen Wissensgebieten, die zufällig aufgelistet werden, zu wählen.   Danach kann der jeweilige Spieler  selbst den Schwierigkeitsgrad bestimmen. 

Für die richtige Beantwortung der leichtesten Frage gibt es einen Punkt, der Schwierigsten sechs Punkte. Sollte die Frage falsch beantwortet werden, bekommnt der Gegner die jeweiligen Punkte gutge- schrieben. 

Ein Spiel besteht aus vier Runden. Gewonnen hat der Spieler mit der höchsten Punkteanzahl.

The game has 3 levels of complexity, you start with words of 4 letters, then words of 6 letters and finally words of 9 letters.Be reassured, if you can not find the correct order of letters one by word, you can ask your friends for help on social networks and other communication media.WORKS OF ART AND ANIMATIONS FUNAt first, a simple box presents itself to you. If you want to discover its contents, you must solve the different puzzles by rearranging the mixed letters of the animal names. Never was a play on words and letters so exciting and fun.QUIZZY ANIMALS CHARACTERISTICS- More than 40 animal names to find- A box full of surprises- An educational and fun game with lots of animal names to discover- Available in 7 languages: French, German, English, Italian, Spanish, Portuguese, Albanian (automatically takes up the language of your device. If none of these languages ​​are configured on your device, English is taken by default)
